{
  "texts": [
    "To complicate this matter further, the point at which the processing of personal data \"reveals\" special categories of personal data under article 9(1) GDPR has not yet been conclusively clarified.",
    "It is worth taking a chronological review of the various data processing operationsused for training the model.",
    "A key consideration is whether data anonymisation occurs during model training.",
    "The prevailing view is that an authorisation basis is required.",
    "In this context, anonymisation is understood as normative rather than technical, in line with the ECJ ruling that holds that data has been anonymised even if it is technically possible, but unlikely, that the controller could carry out identification with the means available including additional information."
  ]
}